article.headline: Montana 83, North Dakota 63
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Jordan Hasquet scored 22 points and Ryan Staudacher added 20 to help Montana to an 83-63 win over North Dakota on Tuesday night. Anthony Johnson added 14 points and had four assists for the Grizzlies (3-4), who snapped a three game losing streak. Montana took a 20-11 lead off a Johnson layup with 9:30 remaining in the first half. Hasquet scored 15 of his 22 points in the first half, including a 3-pointer at the buzzer that gave the Grizzlies a 45-31 halftime lead. Montana took a 23-point lead when Staudacher hit a 3-pointer with 9:20 remaining in the game. He was 7-of-8 from the field, including six three pointers. Daniel Harkins led the Fighting Sioux (4-2) with 16 points, and Travis Bledsoe came off the bench to add 11.
